Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of GNC devices on small robots and their ability to climb off-world canyons, cliffs, and caves. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of distributed control approach and simulation results to evaluate the feasibility of the approach. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of dynamics and control simulation to evaluate the feasibility of the approach. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a multirobot system that works cooperatively to climb a slope. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the software and algorithms used for the guidance, navigation, and control of the multirobot system.
